    "For example, K-Fold Cross-Validation (used in almost 25 studies), cross-validation (used in 23 studies), and hold-out validation (14 studies).",
    "Hold-out validation is suitable for large datasets and involves partitioning of datasets into training, validation, and test data.",
    "Training data are used to train the model, validation data are used to fine-tune the model, and test data are used to assess the performance of the model.",
    "K-fold CV is a robust method that divides datasets into a k number of folds.",
    "One fold was applied for the assessment of the model performance, while the other fold was used for the training of the model."
